(2. Original Proposal Baseline) Tj
/F1 10.20 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 364.20 Tm
(The proposal identified the following core problem:) Tj
/F1 10.20 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 342.00 Tm
(Quote: In group projects, it is difficult to later verify the real contribution of each team) Tj
/F1 10.20 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 327.80 Tm
(member. Existing task tools may track tasks, but they do not provide immutable, timestamped,) Tj
/F1 10.20 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 313.60 Tm
(externally verifiable records of approved contribution evidence.) Tj
/F1 10.20 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 291.40 Tm
(The proposed solution was a blockchain-based Proof-of-Contribution platform where:) Tj
/F1 10.20 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 269.20 Tm
(- Contribution evidence is submitted by project members.) Tj
/F1 10.20 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 255.00 Tm
(- Authorized users approve the evidence.) Tj
/F1 10.20 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 240.80 Tm
(- Approved records are written to blockchain as immutable records.) Tj
/F1 10.20 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 226.60 Tm
(- Contribution records are linked to wallet addresses.) Tj
/F1 10.20 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 212.40 Tm
(- Evidence is represented by GitHub links, file hashes, report hashes, or IPFS CIDs.) Tj
/F1 10.20 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 198.20 Tm
(- Contribution profiles and non-transferable Soulbound badges are eventually issued.) Tj
/F1 10.20 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 176.00 Tm
(The proposal also used the DSRM approach and defined evaluation goals such as verifiability,) Tj
/F1 10.20 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 161.80 Tm
(immutability, authorization, duplicate prevention, and non-transferability of badges.) Tj
/F2 13.00 Tf
1 0 0 1 54.00 133.60 Tm
